    {
      "id": "a51d684fd1e289bf04e99319feacac1574c3a426",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 500,
        "name": "Thomas Stibor",
        "email": "t.stibor@gsi.de",
        "username": "tstibor"
      },
      "date": "2017-12-12 15:15:25.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nHi James,\ndo you mean the option:\nTest-Parameters: clientdistro=sles12sp2,etc...?\nfor checking the patch on all the distros?",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "26f6ee9e5f94c77acdf872219c9694c72e7d1fe8",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 500,
        "name": "Thomas Stibor",
        "email": "t.stibor@gsi.de",
        "username": "tstibor"
      },
      "date": "2017-12-12 15:48:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nWhen you mean the HAVE_STRUCT_POSIX_ACL_XATTR, I am reusing the already provided check:\n\n#\n# LC_STRUCT_POSIX_ACL_XATTR\n#\n# Kernel version 4.8 commit 2211d5ba5c6c4e972ba6dbc912b2897425ea6621\n# posix_acl: xattr representation cleanups\n#\nAC_DEFUN([LC_STRUCT_POSIX_ACL_XATTR], [\nLB_CHECK_COMPILE([if 'struct posix_acl_xattr_{header,entry}' defined],\nstruct_posix_acl_xattr, [\n        #include <linux/fs.h>\n        #include <linux/posix_acl_xattr.h>\n],[\n        struct posix_acl_xattr_header *h = NULL;\n        struct posix_acl_xattr_entry  *e;\n        e = (void *)(h + 1);\n],[\n        AC_DEFINE(HAVE_STRUCT_POSIX_ACL_XATTR, 1,\n                [struct posix_acl_xattr_{header,entry} defined])\n])\n]) # LC_STRUCT_POSIX_ACL_XATTR\n\nfor deciding whether a_entries exists, because the commit\n2211d5ba5c6c4e972ba6dbc912b2897425ea6621\nalso changed:\n...\n-typedef struct {\n+struct posix_acl_xattr_header {\n        __le32                  a_version;\n-       posix_acl_xattr_entry   a_entries[0];\n-} posix_acl_xattr_header;\n+};\n...",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "74dd3c3b345fd8050835a1a2e5d6cff58477ac94",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 125,
        "name": "James Simmons",
        "email": "jsimmons@infradead.org",
        "username": "jsimmons"
      },
      "date": "2017-12-12 16:35:31.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\nOh I see what you are doing. Andreas Gruenbacher removed the wiretest code during the 4.8 cycle to prepare for the eventual removal of a_entries which happened in 4.13 kernel.  It makes sense what you are doing.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "d3f92ebb42064e779633fbe49c8e8ae6971d3c7c",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 147,
        "name": "Maloo",
        "email": "maloo@whamcloud.com",
        "username": "maloo",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2017-12-12 17:12:22.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Verified+1\n\nTests uploaded by Trevis Autotest2 from trevis-49vm5 for review-ldiskfs received by maloo, run on CentOS Linux 7/x86_64: (https://testing.hpdd.intel.com/test_sessions/fcf57200-92a8-480b-a421-41333f6310c0). Ran 5 tests. No failures.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "5d1584f8e9bf45d8ad2dfdb9e7590aa1570b7e32",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 117,
        "name": "Andreas Dilger",
        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2017-12-13 05:20:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review-1\n\nThis file is automatically generated from wirecheck.c, please see check_posix_acl_xattr_entry() for how to handle this.\n\nI thought there was also a comment at the start of wiretest.c, but there isn't.  It would be useful to add something to lustre/ptlrpc/wirehdr.c and lustre/utils/wirehdr.c (which is prepended to the output from wirecheck.c) like:\n\n * This file is automatically generated from wirecheck.c and wirehdr.c\n\nor similar.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "a763e837434733fbd5b900bda5e5473c1d319dd6",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 500,
        "name": "Thomas Stibor",
        "email": "t.stibor@gsi.de",
        "username": "tstibor"
      },
      "date": "2017-12-13 10:18:15.000000000",
      "message": "Uploaded patch set 2.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "530787bd34a74595278bdccc805aadecbb080ef1",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 377,
        "name": "wc-checkpatch",
        "username": "hpdd-checkpatch",
        "tags": [
          "SERVICE_USER"
        ]
      },
      "date": "2017-12-13 10:23:17.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nLooks good to me.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "8ee0ee62e780b33569c83eee3d92f8e677f0cd6a",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 500,
        "name": "Thomas Stibor",
        "email": "t.stibor@gsi.de",
        "username": "tstibor"
      },
      "date": "2017-12-13 10:24:50.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nJust added in:\nstatic void\ncheck_posix_acl_xattr_header(void)\n{\n        ....\n\tprintf(\"#ifndef HAVE_STRUCT_POSIX_ACL_XATTR\\n\");\n\tCHECK_MEMBER_TYPEDEF(posix_acl_xattr_header, a_entries);\n\tprintf(\"#endif /* HAVE_STRUCT_POSIX_ACL_XATTR */\\n\");\n\t...\n}\n\nand then compiled/run with: make -C lustre/utils newwiretest\nwhich created automatically the new updated:\n\nlustre/utils/wirecheck.c and \nluste/ptlrpc/wirechech.c files.\n\nThere is already the text provided, that these files\nare generated via the command, so I did not add any other\ntext at top of the files.\n\nvoid lustre_assert_wire_constants(void)\n{\n        /* Wire protocol assertions generated by 'wirecheck'\n         * (make -C lustre/utils newwiretest)\n         */",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
