      "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\nI applied the patch:\n\n+       printf(\"#ifndef HAVE_STRUCT_POSIX_ACL_XATTR\\n\");\n        CHECK_MEMBER_TYPEDEF(posix_acl_xattr_header, a_entries);\n+       printf(\"#endif /* HAVE_STRUCT_POSIX_ACL_XATTR */\\n\");\n\nand configured on Linux debian-9-lustre 4.9.0-4-amd64 #1 SMP Debian 4.9.65-3 (2017-12-03) x86_64 GNU/Linux\n\nas follows:\n./configure --disable-server\n\nThen I generated the two files:\nlustre/utils/wiretest.c and\nlustre/ptlrpc/wiretest.c\n\nwith\n\nmake -C lustre/utils newwiretest\n\nThis automatically removed the #ifdef HAVE_SERVER_SUPPORT statements in\nlustre/utils/wiretest.c and\nlustre/ptlrpc/wiretest.c\n\nHowever, because that breaks upstream I added the #ifdef statements back by hand.",
